Build a web application called "Field Notes" — a UX portfolio documentation platform for practitioners working in unconventional spaces (retail, hospitality, service environments). The core insight: UX is a mindset, not a job title. This platform helps people document their real work as it happens and turn it into credible portfolio evidence.

---

TECH STACK

- React (Vite)
- Plain CSS (no Tailwind, no UI libraries)
- localStorage for persistence
- No backend, no auth, no database
- Single deployable build via npm run build
- Google Fonts: DM Serif Display (italic) + DM Mono

---

VISUAL IDENTITY — WARM PARCHMENT THEME

The base theme never changes. Only the accent color changes based on user preference.

Base tokens (always fixed):
- --bg:    #f7f5f0  (warm off-white background)
- --bg2:   #f0ede6  (warm secondary surface — changes slightly per accent)
- --ink2:  #5a5750  (secondary text)
- --muted: #9c9890  (muted text)
- --faint: #b0ada6  (faint/hint text)
- --line:  #d0cdc6  (borders and lines)
- --line2: #e8e5e0  (subtle dividers)
- --white: #ffffff  (card surfaces)

Accent system — --ink and --accent are set by the user's chosen theme:

DEFAULT — Ink (black):
  --ink:         #2c2a26
  --accent:      #2c2a26
  --accent-text: #f7f5f0
  --bg2:         #f0ede6
  --active-bg:   #ede9e2

FOREST — Deep forest green:
  --ink:         #2d4a35
  --accent:      #2d4a35
  --accent-text: #f7f5f0
  --bg2:         #e4ede5
  --active-bg:   #dceadd

INDIGO — Deep indigo blue:
  --ink:         #2e3a6e
  --accent:      #2e3a6e
  --accent-text: #f7f5f0
  --bg2:         #e4e6f0
  --active-bg:   #dce0ef

UMBER — Warm dark brown:
  --ink:         #5c3d1e
  --accent:      #5c3d1e
  --accent-text: #f7f5f0
  --bg2:         #ede5da
  --active-bg:   #e8ddd0

PLUM — Deep plum purple:
  --ink:         #4a2d4e
  --accent:      #4a2d4e
  --accent-text: #f7f5f0
  --bg2:         #ece2ee
  --active-bg:   #e6d8e8

Apply the accent by writing the chosen token set onto :root via a data attribute:
  <html data-accent="ink">    → default
  <html data-accent="forest"> → forest green
  etc.

In global.css, define each accent as an attribute selector:
  :root, [data-accent="ink"]    { --ink: #2c2a26; --accent: #2c2a26; ... }
  [data-accent="forest"]        { --ink: #2d4a35; --accent: #2d4a35; ... }
  [data-accent="indigo"]        { --ink: #2e3a6e; --accent: #2e3a6e; ... }
  [data-accent="umber"]         { --ink: #5c3d1e; --accent: #5c3d1e; ... }
  [data-accent="plum"]          { --ink: #4a2d4e; --accent: #4a2d4e; ... }

Save the chosen accent to localStorage under "fieldnotes_accent". Load on mount and apply to document.documentElement.setAttribute("data-accent", value).

Phase colors (fixed regardless of accent — these never change):
  --phase-observe: #7b9cc4
  --phase-define:  #b88fc2
  --phase-ideate:  #8aab7e
  --phase-test:    #d4856a
  --phase-launch:  #9c8060
  --phase-reflect: #9c9890

Typography:
  --font-serif: 'DM Serif Display', Georgia, serif
  --font-mono:  'DM Mono', monospace
  --font-sans:  system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif

Aesthetic rules (non-negotiable):
- NO gradients, NO shadows, NO blur
- 0.5px borders everywhere (not 1px)
- Border radius: 2–3px for components, 0 for single-sided borders
- Feels like an architectural blueprint or a tailor's pattern — precise, minimal, warm
- NEVER feels like a generic SaaS app
- All text: sentence case, never ALL CAPS except small labels (8–10px, letter-spacing 2–3px)
- Logo: DM Serif Display italic always
- Numbers/stats: DM Mono weight 300

