THE RIVER — CORE VISUALIZATION

SVG canvas (viewBox="0 0 580 200"):
- SVG_W=580, SVG_H=200, Y_MIN=22, Y_MAX=178, Y_MID=100, X_START=50, X_END=540
- Left vertical axis + bottom horizontal axis with arrow marker
- Three faint dashed grid lines at y=48, y=100, y=152
- Y-axis labels: "smooth" top-left, "friction" bottom-left (both color: var(--line))
- X-axis label: "time →" far right

River curve:
- Sort moments by x
- Build cubic bezier path: start (X_START, Y_MID) → through each moment → end (X_END, last_y)
- Midpoint control: cx = (prev.x + cur.x) / 2
- Fill under curve: var(--accent) at 4% opacity
- Curve stroke: var(--accent), strokeWidth 2, opacity 0.65

Each moment dot:
- Outer pulse: phase color, r=11 (active: r=15), opacity 0.13
- Inner dot: phase color, r=5 (active: r=7), stroke white 1.5px
- Title: 8px, font-weight 500, var(--ink), truncated at 17 chars
- Subtitle: 7px, var(--muted), offset 11px from title
- Label position: above dot if dot is below midline, below dot if above midline

getSvgPoint function:
  const rect = svg.getBoundingClientRect()
  return {
    x: (clientX - rect.left) * (SVG_W / rect.width),
    y: (clientY - rect.top)  * (SVG_H / rect.height)
  }

Interactions:
- Click empty canvas → create moment at coordinates
- Click dot → open edit panel
- Drag dot vertically → update y in real time, river redraws
- Hover dot → show artifact tooltip
- Touch support for all interactions

Empty state: italic serif placeholder text centered in SVG

